[30;1m684 | [0m[35mdef authenticate_password(controller, password, suppress_ctl_errors = True):[0m
[30;1m685 | [0m[35m  """[0m
[30;1m686 | [0m[35m  Authenticates to a control socket that uses a password (via the[0m
[30;1m687 | [0m[35m  HashedControlPassword torrc option). Quotes in the password are escaped.[0m
[30;1m688 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m689 | [0m[35m  If authentication fails tor will disconnect and we'll make a best effort[0m
[30;1m690 | [0m[35m  attempt to re-establish the connection. This may not succeed, so check[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m361[0m[34m of [0m[33m2534[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000701[0m

   Rule Id: [34mBD000701[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Token[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mHigh[0m
  Filename: [33m/stem-1.8.2/docs/faq.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m(npm owner|password|htpasswd|auth_?token|secret_?key|private_?key|authorized_keys?|npmrc|\.ssh|usersecrets?|api_?keys|nuget\.config|\.identityservice)[0m
[30;1m206 | [0m[35m**I'm using safe cookie authentication**[0m
[30;1m207 | [0m[35m~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~[0m
[30;1m208 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m209 | [0m[35mPassword and cookie authentication both disclose your credential. This makes[0m
[30;1m210 | [0m[35myou vulnerable to replay attacks if you accidently connect to a malicious port[0m
[30;1m211 | [0m[35mor have a man-in-the-middle. **SAFECOOKIE** authentication avoids this through[0m
[30;1m212 | [0m[35ma two way handshake, but authenticating by hand requires some extra work.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m480[0m[34m of [0m[33m2534[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000701[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Token[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mHigh[0m
  Filename: [33m/stem-1.8.2/docs/faq.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m(npm owner|password|htpasswd|auth_?token|secret_?key|private_?key|authorized_keys?|npmrc|\.ssh|usersecrets?|api_?keys|nuget\.config|\.identityservice)[0m
[30;1m114 | [0m[35mIf you are using a **ControlPort** then the easiest method of talking with Tor[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35mis via **telnet**. You always need to authenticate after connecting, even if[0m
[30;1m116 | [0m[35mTor does not restrict access. If your torrc doesn't have a[0m
[30;1m117 | [0m[35m**CookieAuthentication** or **HashedControlPassword** then to authenticate you[0m
[30;1m118 | [0m[35mwill simply call **AUTHENTICATE** after connecting without any credentials.[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m120 | [0m[35m::[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m481[0m[34m of [0m[33m2534[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000701[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Token[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mHigh[0m
  Filename: [33m/stem-1.8.2/docs/faq.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m(npm owner|password|htpasswd|auth_?token|secret_?key|private_?key|authorized_keys?|npmrc|\.ssh|usersecrets?|api_?keys|nuget\.config|\.identityservice)[0m
[30;1m103 | [0m[35m  have neither then Tor will not accept controller connections.[0m
[30;1m104 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m105 | [0m[35m* What type of authentication is Tor's controller interface using? This is[0m
[30;1m106 | [0m[35m  defined by your **CookieAuthentication** or **HashedControlPassword** option.[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35m  If you have neither then Tor does not restrict access.[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35mWe'll tackle each of these scenarios one at a time...[0m

[30;1m364 | [0m[35mdef is_available(command, cached=True):[0m
[30;1m365 | [0m[35m  """[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m2100[0m[34m of [0m[33m2534[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m461 | [0m[35m  :var str path: hidden service directory[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m385 | [0m[35m* Metrics-lib and Stem can both read from compressed tarballs at a small[0m

[30;1m387 | [0m[35m  <../faq.html#how-do-i-read-tar-xz-descriptor-archives>`_ consensus in[0m
[30;1m388 | [0m[35m  **255.76 ms** and Stem can do it in **902.75 ms**.[0m
